    <!-- ========== ENGLISH ========== -->
    <div class="lang active" data-lang="en" id="panel-en" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-en" aria-hidden="false" tabindex="0">
      <div class="note">Follow the steps that match your treatment.</div>

      <div class="layout">
        <nav class="toc" aria-label="On this page">
          <h3>Content</h3>
          <a href="#en-implants">Implants</a>
          <a href="#en-implant-signs">Signs of Implant Issues</a>
          <a href="#en-sinus">Sinus Lift Procedure</a>
          <a href="#en-pmma">Temporary PMMA Restorations</a>
          <a href="#en-crowns">Crowns</a>
        </nav>

        <main>
          <section id="en-implants" class="card">
            <img class="card-hero-img" alt="Implants" loading="lazy"
              src="https://images.assets-landingi.com/uc/669e38e2-b039-4022-b731-45eb2bd84ad0/implant.jpg"/>

            <details open>
              <summary>Oral Hygiene Instructions<span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">›</span></summary>
              <div class="content">
                <ul>
                  <li>Brush at least twice a day, ideally within 30–60 minutes after meals.</li>
                  <li>Use a new soft-bristled toothbrush.</li>
                  <li>Use gentle circular motions around the implant area.</li>
                  <li>Choose a non-abrasive toothpaste to avoid scratching the surface.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary>Mouthwash & Rinsing<span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">›</span></summary>
              <div class="content">
                <ul>
                  <li>Avoid alcohol-based mouthwashes.</li>
                  <li>Rinse with salted water for 20–30 seconds, 2–3 times daily, especially after meals.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary>Healing & Habits<span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">›</span></summary>
              <div class="content">
                <ul>
                  <li>No smoking for at least two weeks post-surgery.</li>
                  <li>Limit alcohol; it may slow healing and interact with medication.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary>Diet Guidance<span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">›</span></summary>
              <div class="content">
                <ul>
                  <li>Prefer a soft diet for the first few days.</li>
                  <li>Avoid hot, spicy, or crunchy foods while healing.</li>
                  <li>Limit sugary and acidic foods.</li>
                  <li>Do not chew hard items like ice or pens.</li>
                  <li>Avoid toothpicks or blunt objects around the gums.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </details>
          </section>

          <section id="en-implant-signs" class="card">
            <img class="card-hero-img" alt="Signs of implant issues" loading="lazy"
              src="https://images.assets-landingi.com/uc/dfad7ae4-9975-42c5-ad9b-3f53dbce8a33/SignsofImplantIssues.jpg"/>

            <details open>
              <summary>When to Contact Dentakay After-Care Team<span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">›</span></summary>
              <div class="content">
                <ul>
                  <li>Redness, swelling, pain, or unusual mobility around the implant. If noted, contact our after-care representative promptly.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </details>
          </section>

          <section id="en-sinus" class="card">
            <img class="card-hero-img" alt="Sinus lift procedure" loading="lazy"
              src="https://images.assets-landingi.com/uc/682f9f31-b8b9-4b54-96f4-79f771a818e8/SinusLiftProcedure1.jpg"/>

            <details open>
              <summary>Pressure Control & Activity<span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">›</span></summary>
              <div class="content">
                <ul>
                  <li>Avoid sneezing, coughing, or blowing your nose for 2–3 weeks. If you must sneeze, keep your mouth open.</li>
                  <li>No heavy lifting, bending, or vigorous exercise that increases sinus pressure.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary>Habits & Rinsing<span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">›</span></summary>
              <div class="content">
                <ul>
                  <li>Avoid smoking for the first 2–3 months.</li>
                  <li>No straws for at least 1–2 weeks.</li>
                  <li>Brush and rinse gently, avoiding the surgical site.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </details>
          </section>

          <section id="en-pmma" class="card">
            <img class="card-hero-img" alt="Temporary PMMA restorations" loading="lazy"
              src="https://images.assets-landingi.com/uc/31039dcd-3fd8-49e7-a94c-9e2ec1a27108/TemporaryPMMARestorations.jpg"/>

            <details open>
              <summary>Purpose & Limitations<span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">›</span></summary>
              <div class="content">
                <ul>
                  <li>Not designed for chewing or biting. Avoid hard or sticky foods like nuts, crusts, gum, ice, or tough meat.</li>
                  <li>Main purpose is aesthetic during healing.</li>
                  <li>Do not test their strength on hard foods.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary>Cleaning Routine<span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">›</span></summary>
              <div class="content">
                <ul>
                  <li>Brush gently twice daily with a soft brush and non-abrasive toothpaste.</li>
                  <li>Rinse daily with a non-alcoholic mouthwash.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </details>
          </section>

          <section id="en-crowns" class="card">
            <img class="card-hero-img" alt="Crowns" loading="lazy"
              src="https://images.assets-landingi.com/uc/65ddbbe9-4da8-479f-b1cc-18d8ead12edb/crowns.jpg"/>

            <details open>
              <summary>Daily Care<span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">›</span></summary>
              <div class="content">
                <ul>
                  <li>Use a new soft-bristled toothbrush and non-abrasive toothpaste twice daily.</li>
                  <li>Use daily mouthwash to control bacteria. Avoid alcohol-based products.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </details>
            <details>
              <summary>Eating & Sensitivity<span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">›</span></summary>
              <div class="content">
                <ul>
                  <li>Avoid sticky and hard foods that increase pressure.</li>
                  <li>Limit sugary foods and drinks to protect crown margins.</li>
                  <li>If sensitivity occurs, avoid very hot or cold foods for a time.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </details>
          </section>
        </main>
      </div>
    </div>
